	<u><strong>ABOUT THE GIG</strong></u></p>
<p>
	FUSION (www.thefusionagency.com) is looking for an INTERACTIVE MEDIA DEVELOPER +PROGRAMMER to join our thriving digital team and translate clients&#39; business goals into successful digital strategies.</p>
<p>
	Responsibilities would include the creation and development of client&rsquo;s websites, mobile sites, mobile applications and micro-sites as well as on-site SEO strategies.</p>
<p>
	You will collaborate with FUSION team members, integrating digital strategies into a broader client strategy.</p>
<p>
	&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	<u><strong>REQUIREMENTS</strong></u></p>
<p>
	*BA/BS in Information Technology, Information Systems, MIS, eCommerce, Computer Science or related discipline (An equivalent combination of education and experience may be considered).</p>
<p>
	*Develop rich web user interfaces that interface with back-end components using PHP, CSS3 HTML 5 and Javascript.</p>
<p>
	*Support applications and tools used for content management, e-commerce, social networking and other types of web publishing.</p>
<p>
	*3-5 years of PHP system architecture and development.</p>
<p>
	*Can demonstrate expertise with HTML, Javascript frameworks (jQuery a plus), CSS, Ajax, HTML5, Source control (SVN).</p>
<p>
	*Familiarity with open source content management systems a plus (such as Wordpress, Drupal and Joomla).</p>
<p>
	*Must be an effective communicator, highly-motivated and detail-oriented.</p>
<p>
	*Must be able to work independently with minimum supervision and be a valuable contributor in an interactive team environment.</p>
<p>
	*Strong communication skills (written and verbal), interpersonal skills, a positive attitude and the ability to thrive in a collaborative environment.</p>
<p>
	*Able to successfully organize, prioritize and manage multiple projects in a deadline-driven environment.</p>
<p>
	*Proficient juggler (or any circus-like skills).</p>
<p>
	*Effective troubleshooting and problem-solving skills.</p>
<p>
	*Ability to quickly and clearly examine algorithmic best practices, opportunities and solutions that are applicable to a site property.</p>
<p>
	*Passion for excellence, digital marketing, and overall intellectual curiosity.</p>
<p>
	*Solid understanding of shopping &amp; comparison search engines, data feed creation, local search, spec requirements, implementation issues, and QA for various uploads.</p>
<p>
	*Proficiency in design applications such InDesign, Illustrator, and Photoshop, a plus.</p>
<p>
	*Proven ability to help larger team implement and push ongoing strategic projects for algorithmic growth.</p>
<p>
	*Stays current with industry best practices and web technologies.</p>
<p>
	*Participation in creating white papers, POV&#39;s, blog posts, or industry thought leadership.</p>
<p>
